# Code conventions

## Vue components

- Use the **Composition API** with `<script setup lang="ts">` exclusively. No Options API.
- Components derive visual state from the store — never store derived values in `ref()` inside a component when a `computed()` reading from the store suffices.
- `WordCell.vue` is the canonical example: it holds no local state, everything comes from `useGameStore()`.

## Composables

- Pure logic goes into composables under `src/composables/`. No component imports, no Pinia store imports unless the composable explicitly bridges DOM ↔ store (like `useSelection.ts`).
- Composable functions are named `useXxx` and return a plain object of refs and handlers.

## No external UI framework

Plain CSS in scoped `<style>` blocks only. No Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS, no component libraries.

## TypeScript

- All exported types live in the file that owns the data. Store types (`Cell`, `PlacedWord`, `Difficulty`, `Direction`) are exported from `gameStore.ts`; word types from `wordLists.ts`.
- Avoid `any`. Use `unknown` or a proper interface.

## Touch handling

Touch events are bound at the **container level** in `WordGrid.vue`, not per-cell, to avoid hundreds of listeners. The cell coordinates are read from `data-row` / `data-col` attributes via `document.elementFromPoint`.
